SUMMARY:Support Over Solitude – Virtual
DESCRIPTION:This teen grief support group is open to youth ages 13–18 who have lost a parent\, sibling\, or other significant person. Participants will meet virtually to name their experiences of grief\, build positive coping skills\, and connect with other teens who have similar experiences. \nThursdays\, 6:00–7:00pm\nJanuary 15\, 29\nFebruary 12\, 26\nMarch 19\nApril 2 \nPLEASE NOTE: Please note\, our registration process has changed. If you are interested in a child or teen grief support program or group\, please call 919-719-7199\, email kidsgrief@transitionslifecare.org\, or use the following link to contact us: Contact Us 24/7 – Transitions LifeCare. A grief counselor will connect with you to talk through your child’s needs and determine whether a group is the right fit.
URL:https://www.transitionslifecare.org/event/support-over-solitude-virtual-2/2026-03-19/
LOCATION:Virtual
CATEGORIES:Grief Support,Kids Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.transitionslifecare.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/TGC-SOS-Graphic.jpg
GEO:35.7595731;-79.0192997
